---
import { siteConfig } from "../../config";
import "../../styles/global.css";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="In-app payment flow using Stripe Elements and PaymentIntents API in Flutter."
    />
    <title>Stripe Payment Flow · {siteConfig.name}</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto p-8">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Stripe Payment Flow</h1>

      <p class="mb-6 text-gray-700">
        Flutter implementation of a robust payment system using Stripe — including saved cards and secure payment flows.
      </p>

      <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
        <li>Built with Flutter and Dart</li>
        <li>Integrated Stripe Elements for secure card input</li>
        <li>Used PaymentIntents API to support both one-time and saved-card payments</li>
        <li>Custom UI with validation, error handling, and loading states</li>
        <li>Displays a list of saved cards with ability to delete</li>
        <li>Tested across platforms with mock payment data</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="grid gap-6">
        <div>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">Adding and using a card</p>
          <video class="w-full rounded-lg border border-gray-300" controls>
            <source src="/assets/flutter_stripe.mov" type="video/mp4" />
            Your browser does not support the video tag.
          </video>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">Managing saved cards</p>
          <video class="w-full rounded-lg border border-gray-300" controls>
            <source src="/assets/flutter_stripe_card_management.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
            Your browser does not support the video tag.
          </video>
        </div>
      </div>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
